oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Parts department of Kittrell Motor Company
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Parts department of Kittrell Motor Company. The two people shown are Orville and Hettie Grimes.

Kittrell Motor Company was established in 1921 by brothers Will and G.H. Kittrell. They sold several makes of cars, with a focus on Chevrolets. During World War II, Kittrell Motor Company sold livestock feed and gasoline. In 1965, the Kittrell family sold the garage, and it became a Chevrolet dealership.
